ct required skills: Python, Django, React, Node.js, AWS services (EC2, S3, Lambda), CI/CD tools (Docker, Kubernetes, Jenkins), Agile/Scrum.\\n   - Extracted responsibilities: design workflows, automate processes, perform text analysis, email automation.\\n   - Defined evaluation criteria: technical skills (NLP, data extraction, email automation), soft skills (communication, problem-solving), cultural fit.\\n\\n2. Analyze Candidate Resume:\\n   - Parsed John Doe’s resume.\\n   - Identified skills: Python, Django, React, AWS (EC2, S3, Lambda), Docker, Kubernetes; limited TypeScript and mobile dev.\\n   - Calculated:\\n     • Skills Alignment Score: 90/100\\n     • Experience Relevance Score: 85/100\\n     • Overall Match Score: 88/100\\n   - Conclusion: Strong technical foundation, minor gaps in mobile and TypeScript.\\n\\n3. Initial Candidate Screening:\\n   - Compared resume scores against threshold (overall ≥ 75).\\n   - John Doe passed initial screening (88 > 75).\\n   - Decision: Invite for technical interview.\\n\\n4. Send Interview Invitation Email:\\n   Subject: Interview Invitation – Workflow Planning Agent\\n   Body:\\n     Dear John Doe,\\n\\n     We are pleased to invite you to an interview for the Workflow Planning Agent position at Acme Corp. Your skills and experience align well with the role. The interview is scheduled for 2024-05-12 at 10:00 AM via Zoom.\\n\\n     During the interview, we will discuss your experience with NLP, text analysis, data extraction, workflow design, and email automation.\\n\\n     Please confirm your availability at your earliest convenience.\\n\\n     Best regards,\\n     Jane Smith\\n     Talent Acquisition, Acme Corp\\n\\n5. Conduct Technical Interview (2024-05-12 via Zoom):\\n   Question 1: “Describe your experience with Natural Language Processing (NLP). What NLP techniques have you used, and for what purposes?”\\n     - Candidate Response Summary: \\n         Used NLTK and spaCy for tokenization, POS tagging, and named entity recognition; built sentiment analysis models using scikit-learn; experimented with Hugging Face transformers for text classification in a customer feedback project.\\n     - Score: 8/10\\n     - Rationale: Broad range of NLP tools, hands-on experience, but limited large-scale production deployment experience.\\n     - Red Flags: None significant.\\n\\n   Question 2: “Explain your approach to text analysis. How do you handle unstructured text data, and what methods do you use to extract meaningful information?”\\n     - Candidate Response Summary:\\n         Pipeline: data cleaning (regex, stop-word removal), tokenization, lemmatization; extracted topic clusters via LDA; applied word embeddings (Word2Vec) for semantic search.\\n     - Score: 7/10\\n     - Rationale: Solid methodology, good theoretical understanding; limited discussion of performance optimization.\\n     - Red Flags: Some uncertainty around scaling to large datasets.\\n\\n   Question 3: “Describe a project where you automated data extraction from documents or web pages. What tools and techniques did you use?”\\n     - Candidate Response Summary:\\n         Developed a scraper using Python, BeautifulSoup, and Selenium; parsed HTML, extracted product information to JSON; automated daily runs via cron and monitored with AWS Lambda.\\n     - Score: 9/10\\n     - Rationale: Clear project vision, robust automation, good use of AWS for scheduling.\\n     - Red Flags: None.\\n\\n   Question 4: “How would you design a workflow to analyze customer reviews and identify key areas for product improvement?”\\n     - Candidate Response Summary:\\n         Proposed workflow: ingest reviews via API → preprocess (clean, normalize) → sentiment analysis → topic modeling → dashboard visualization in Tableau → automated weekly email reports.\\n     - Score: 8/10\\n     - Rationale: Comprehensive end-to-end design, practical tool choices; could elaborate on monitoring and data retention.\\n     - Red Flags: None.\\n\\n   Question 5: “How familiar are you with email automation? Describe any experience you have in automating email sending or processing.”\\n     - Candidate Response Summary:\\n         Used SendGrid API and AWS SES to send transactional emails; built workflows in Zapier for triggered notifications; integrated email parsing with AWS Lambda for inbound processing.\\n     - Score: 7/10\\n     - Rationale: Practical experience, but limited to small-scale scripts.\\n     - Red Flags: None.\\n\\n6. Score Candidate Responses:\\n   - Technical Skills Aggregate Score: (8 + 7 + 9 + 8 + 7) / 5 = 7.8/10 → 78/100\\n   - Soft Skills & Communication: 8/10 → 80/100\\n   - Overall Interview Performance Score: (78 + 80) / 2 = 79/100\\n\\n7. Generate Final Evaluation Report:\\n   Candidate Name: John Doe\\n   Interview Date: 2024-05-12\\n\\n   I. Resume Analysis Summary:\\n      - Skills Alignment Score: 90/100\\n      - Experience Relevance Score: 85/100\\n      - Overall Match Score: 88/100\\n      - Fit Assessment: Strong Fit\\n\\n   II. Technical Interview Performance:\\n      - Question 1 (NLP Experience): 8/10\\n      - Question 2 (Text Analysis): 7/10\\n      - Question 3 (Data Extraction): 9/10\\n      - Question 4 (Workflow Design): 8/10\\n      - Question 5 (Email Automation): 7/10\\n      - Aggregate Technical Score: 78/100\\n      - Soft Skills Score: 80/100\\n\\n   III. Overall Strengths:\\n      - Strong Python and NLP toolkit experience.\\n      - Hands-on automation using AWS and CI/CD tools.\\n      - Clear approach to workflow design and data pipelines.\\n\\n   IV. Areas for Improvement:\\n      - Experience with large-scale model deployment.\\n      - Limited exposure to TypeScript and mobile development.\\n\\n   V. Overall Recommendation:\\n      - Hire\\n\\n   VI. Justification:\\n      John Doe demonstrates solid technical competencies in NLP, text analysis, and automation. His hands-on project experience with web scraping and AWS scheduling shows he can implement end-to-end workflows. Communication skills are clear and structured. Minor gaps in large-scale deployments and TypeScript do not outweigh his strong fit for the Workflow Planning Agent role.\\n\\n==============================\\nEnd of Report\\n==============================\\n```\"}"}
